    "instruction": "Load metric.csv (parse timestamp as pd.to_datetime(..., unit='s', utc=True')). Restrict analysis to the five possible root-cause services: checkoutservice, currencyservice, emailservice, productcatalogservice, recommendationservice. For each distinct (cmdb_id, kpi_name) pair among those services: \n1) Compute global P95 and P5 on the full available series for that pair and the total row count (use all timestamps in the file). \n2) Filter the pair's rows to the incident window 2024-01-16 06:54:01 UTC through 2024-01-16 07:24:01 UTC (inclusive). Compute window_count. \n3) Within the window, count anomalies_high as number of rows with value >= global P95, and anomalies_low as number of rows with value <= global P5. For each pair with window_count > 0, return a compact table (limit to top 50 rows) with columns: cmdb_id, kpi_name, total_count, p95, p5, window_count, anomalies_high, anomalies_low, earliest_anomaly_timestamp (UTC, earliest timestamp among anomaly_high or anomaly_low; NULL if none). \nReturn results as a JSON-friendly table/dictionary only (no plots, no raw full time series)."
