{
    "analysis": "Previous steps: we loaded all telemetry and found a high-volume of identical frontend error logs around 2024-01-16T07:11:17Z complaining \"could not retrieve currencies: rpc error...\". Metric anomaly scan for the five candidate services showed strong, persistent anomalies starting around 2024-01-16T06:57:00Z: notably currencyservice.error had every in-window sample flagged, checkoutservice.socket was fully anomalous in-window, and productcatalogservice/emailservice showed diskio/socket anomalies. This suggests a service-level RPC failure on the currency retrieval path (frontend -> currencyservice) that began earlier and manifested in frontend request errors by ~07:11. To localize the root service, we must inspect traces to see which service calls show elevated error_rate, reduced row_count, or latency anomalies during the incident window and which faulty service is most downstream in the failing trace chains. No trace analysis has been executed yet.",
