    "instruction": "Load metric.csv and log.csv (parse timestamp column with pd.to_datetime(..., unit='s', utc=True')). Focus only on cmdb_id == 'currencyservice'. For each distinct kpi_name for currencyservice: \n1) Compute global P95 and P5 using the full available series for that (currencyservice,kpi_name) pair. \n2) Filter to the incident window 2024-01-16 06:54:01 UTC through 2024-01-16 07:24:01 UTC inclusive. Compute: window_count, anomalies_high (value >= global P95), anomalies_low (value <= global P5), earliest_anomaly_timestamp (UTC) among anomalies or NULL, window_max, window_median. \nReturn a compact table (all currencyservice kpi_names, limit to 50 rows) with columns: kpi_name, total_count, p95, p5, window_count, anomalies_high, anomalies_low, earliest_anomaly_timestamp, window_max, window_median. \nAdditionally, return any log.csv rows for currencyservice within the incident window (columns: timestamp, cmdb_id, log_name, value) limited to top 20 rows."
}

